public interface StackPush

The implementing instruction is known to push an element onto the operand stack of the currently executed frame.

Version:
1.0.0, 2010-03-11
Author:
Tim Majchrzak

Method Detail

getNumberOfPushedElements

int getNumberOfPushedElements()
Get the number of elements that will be pushed onto the stack when this instruction is executed. If the number of elements is variable, this method will return the minimum number of elements popped. In this case, VariablyStackPush should be implemented by the instruction.

Returns:
The number of elements that will be pushed onto the stack.

getTypePushed

byte getTypePushed(ClassFile methodClassFile)
Get the type of elements this instruction will push onto the stack.

Parameters:
methodClassFile - The class file of the method this instruction belongs to.
Returns:
The type this instruction pushes. Types are ClassFile.T_BOOLEAN, ClassFile.T_BYTE ClassFile.T_CHAR, ClassFile.T_DOUBLE, ClassFile.T_FLOAT, ClassFile.T_INT, ClassFile.T_LONG and ClassFile.T_SHORT, 0 to indicate a reference or return address type or -1 to indicate the pushed type cannot be determined statically.
